@node about " Setup - by Marty of GREMLiNS BBS"
@prev main
@{"°°" link grems}
   ___  _              _
  / _ \| |__  ___ _  _| |_
 |  _  | '_ \/ _ \ || |  _|
 |_| |_|_.__/\___/\_,_|\__|                          @{b}(c) GREMLiNS MAXsWARE@{ub}

 On Gremlins BBS, I've done many little things to enhance the BBS and make
 it look and work better than the standard setup as most BBS's would have.
 One of these little things is the way I've set up the default  BBS config
 options (eg: Ansi on/off, suburb change, etc..), which is all in one door
 and not a whole menu of each seperate config option as most do?!  So here
 is this new little creation called "Setup" for all you great MAXs SysOp's
 out there (except the lazy ones) who want something different and better!

 It basically is one door with each BBS (MAXs) config setting, but cooler!
 The options (BBS settings) and layout the door offers are used during the
 new user login sequence, after the prompt "Is your name right?". The door
 uses the BBS config prompts from the MAXs text config, as  does the login
 sequence. If unsure, @{"install" link run} "Setup" and run  door, as well as login as a
 new user and see for yourself. You'll enjoy the new look and feel. CooL!?

@endnode
@node run " Setup - by Marty of GREMLiNS BBS"
@{"°°" link grems}
  ___         _        _ _
 |_ _|_ _  __| |_ __ _| | |
  | || ' \(_-<  _/ _` | | |
 |___|_||_/__/\__\__,_|_|_|                          @{b}(c) GREMLiNS MAXsWARE@{ub}

 Firstly (if you already haven't) create a new directory called "gremlins"
 in your doors directory. Assign "gremlins" to your doors path in the user
 startup sequence, eg: "assign gremlins doors:gremlins", assuming you have
 the doors path assigned also (you should have, spastic).

 Move the "Setup" directory (you unpacked) into the "gremlins" dir.  Also,
 move all files in the "Setup_text" dir  into the BBS text path.  Now edit
 the MAXs menu config, set the door to run from a key option (via a menu):

 Eg:  U   34   0   0   10000   gremlins:setup/setup

 That's the easy stuff done, now  you must make changes to  the BBS config
 prompts which MAXs uses, in the MAXs text config (eg: ansi on/off, etc.).
 The following lines are to be changed (see "setup_help.iff" for info):

   9: <BBS:text/ansi_setup.txt
  10: ^MDo you want screen clearing codes (Yes/n)?
  11: ^[[10;3HDo you want a pause after each full screen (Yes/n)?
  12: ^[[8;3HDo you want to use the full screen editor (Yes/n)?
  13: ^[[11;3HHow many lines per screen (24-28)?
  14: ^[[13;3HWhat is your home suburb?
  15: ^[[14;3HWhat is real home phone number?
  16: ^[[15;3HWhat computer do you use?
  17: <BBS:text/password_setup.txt
  18: ^[[23;3HEnter again for verification:
  19:    No match! Try again...%Y%Y
  20: <BBS:text/correct_setup.txt
  30: ^MInitial login complete, adding %f to userbase..
 263: ^M^[[A  Enter the default xfer protcol:  ^[[30;40m^[[1D^[[0m
 275: ^[[9;3HDo you want to recieve junk mail (Msgs to all)?

 Lines 10 and 11 are only used when a new user logs in the first time, and
 are not used in the Setup door as I believe these should always be ON for
 better results (trust me,  I've been doing this longer enough).  Lines 20
 and 30 are are only used during new user login. You may add colour to the
 above lines, as you please where possible, eg: "^[[32mGreen^[[0m".

 When a new user logs in (after "Is your name right?"), Line 9  which is a
 text file will be displayed to clear the screen and start the BBS options
 for the new user (you know which ones), and so forth. When you run Setup,
 the door, and you select [1] Ansi on/off, it shows this text file as well
 and thus clears the screen (this is the only drawback to the door).  Line
 17 and 20 are also small text files, but self explanatory. Also, you need
 to use the additional text files, eg: "ProtocolList(Menu).text" to ensure
 that everything looks and works fine. Backup anything you have too.

 When Setup is run,  selecting [0] displays some exciting information.  To
 exit the Setup door, just hit any other key. Also, upon selecting [5] and
 [6], Setup will advice no changes can be made and user has to leave a msg
 to tell the SysOp of his(her) new details (a good idea?). If you wish the
 user to be able to change these 2 options then use the "Setup-2" door and
 rename it to "Setup".

 You can change the colour and parts of the "Setup.menu" if you wish,  but
 not too much as it may  spoil things,  but feel free to  do as you please
 anyways (if you have any idea).

 Wooah, I've written too much. I think that's all you need to know for now
 but if you need @{"assistance" link all} (or need to contact me), then do so!

@endnode
